topic.title: Developing an online geocoders with AI
topic.text:
https://ufl.zoom.us/rec/share/i4uaoXTyGqGiKugI-PZzkoHIf18PbMWEiAkxTj3ukZaetLzQanIXAs6W60Ea0SZE.lbFhy2aAf2oHAvlN?startTime=1740148768000 
Dr. Sounny discussed the development of a website and a geocoder, focusing on public engagement with remote sensing results and the potential for incorporating AI for improved programming. He also demonstrated the use of AI models through the GitHub student developer pack, and discussed the process of launching a code space and working with a remote repository. Lastly, he discussed the functionalities of GeoJSON, the benefits of using AI for web development, and the process of developing a model to predict malaria outbreaks.
